@andydavis1 You can close the issus.
I have checked the `master branch`, and the typo has been fixed by the commit which @ivmarkp referenced. The reason why it still exists is that the `tensorflow.org` show you the tutorial of `r0.10 branch` . So, when the next version(maybe v0.11) comes, the problem will be fixed automatically.
